      "item": {
        "id": "334527fc-9b88-4b1a-b157-7128fb036fdc",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "As early as 1929, two Melbourne commercial radio stations, [[3UZ]] and 3DB ([[KIIS 101.1]]) were conducting experimental mechanical television broadcasts – these were conducted in the early hours of the morning, after the stations had officially closed down. In 1934 Dr Val McDowall at amateur station [[4CM]] Brisbane conducted experiments in electronic television."
