        "text": "All stations operated under a unique [[Sealed Set]] system under which each set was sealed to the frequency of one station. Part of the price of the set went to the government via the [[Postmaster-General's Department]] (PMG), with money also going to the broadcaster.  Apart from extremely limited advertising, this was the broadcasters' only source of income.  From the outset problems with the system came to the fore. Many young people built their own sets, which could receive all the stations."
      },
